<DocsLayout title="Brokers — Dokkimi Docs" description="Add message brokers like RabbitMQ to your test environment with transparent message log interception.">
  <h1>Brokers</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Add message brokers to your test environment. Dokkimi deploys a transparent proxy sidecar that captures all published and delivered messages without modifying wire traffic.</p>

  <h2>Required fields</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>type</code></td><td><code>"BROKER"</code></td><td>Item type</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>name</code></td><td>string</td><td>Unique name (1-63 chars). Used as DNS hostname for service connections.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>broker</code></td><td>enum</td><td><code>"amqp"</code></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Optional fields</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>description</code></td><td>string</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>Human-readable description (max 500 chars)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>image</code></td><td>string</td><td>per engine</td><td>Custom Docker image (e.g. <code>"rabbitmq:3.13-management"</code>)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>port</code></td><td>integer</td><td>per engine</td><td>Native broker port</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>healthCheck</code></td><td>string</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>Health check endpoint or <code>"tcp"</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>env</code></td><td>array</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>Environment variables: <code>[&#123; "name": "KEY", "value": "VALUE" &#125;]</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>command</code></td><td>string[]</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>Override Docker image CMD</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>minCpu</code></td><td>number</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>Minimum CPU cores</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>minMemory</code></td><td>number</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>Minimum memory in MB</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>maxCpu</code></td><td>number</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>Maximum CPU cores</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>maxMemory</code></td><td>number</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>Maximum memory in MB</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Engine details</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Engine</th><th>Default image</th><th>Native port</th><th>Default connection string</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>amqp</code></td><td>rabbitmq:3</td><td>5672</td><td><code>amqp://guest:guest@&#123;name&#125;:5672</code></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <p>When you add a BROKER item, Dokkimi deploys a <strong>broker-proxy</strong> sidecar alongside the broker container. The proxy sits between your services and the broker, transparently relaying all wire protocol frames. It inspects publish and deliver operations to capture message metadata and bodies, which become available as <code>$.messageLogs</code> in your test assertions.</p>
  <p>Your services connect to the broker using the item's <code>name</code> as the hostname and the broker's native port (5672 for AMQP). No code changes needed &mdash; the proxy is invisible to your application.</p>

  <h2>Examples</h2>

  <h3>Basic RabbitMQ</h3>
  <CodeBlock code={`{
  "type": "BROKER",
  "name": "rabbitmq",
  "broker": "amqp"
}`} lang="json" />

  <h3>Custom image with credentials</h3>
  <CodeBlock code={`{
  "type": "BROKER",
  "name": "rabbitmq",
  "broker": "amqp",
  "image": "rabbitmq:3.13-management",
  "env": [
    { "name": "RABBITMQ_DEFAULT_USER", "value": "myuser" },
    { "name": "RABBITMQ_DEFAULT_PASS", "value": "mypass" }
  ]
}`} lang="json" />

  <h3>As a shared fragment (YAML)</h3>
  <CodeBlock code={`# .dokkimi/shared/rabbitmq.yaml
type: BROKER
name: rabbitmq
broker: amqp`} lang="yaml" />

  <h2>Connecting services</h2>
  <p>Use the broker item's <code>name</code> as the hostname in your service's environment variables:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={`{
  "type": "SERVICE",
  "name": "order-service",
  "image": "order-service:latest",
  "port": 3000,
  "healthCheck": "/health",
  "env": [
    { "name": "AMQP_URL", "value": "amqp://guest:guest@rabbitmq:5672" }
  ]
}`} lang="json" />

  <h2>Asserting on message logs</h2>
  <p>Captured messages are available via <code>$.messageLogs</code> in wait step assertions. Each entry contains:</p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>broker</code></td><td>Broker item name</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>brokerType</code></td><td>Protocol type (e.g. <code>"amqp"</code>)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>operation</code></td><td><code>"publish"</code> or <code>"deliver"</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>body</code></td><td>Message body (parsed JSON or raw string)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>timestamp</code></td><td>ISO timestamp</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>AMQP messages also include <code>exchange</code> and <code>routingKey</code> fields.</p>

  <h3>Example: verify a publish was logged</h3>
  <CodeBlock code={`{
  "name": "Verify message was published",
  "action": { "type": "wait", "durationMs": 500 },
  "assertions": [
    {
      "assertions": [
        { "count": "$.messageLogs", "operator": "gte", "value": 1 },
        { "path": "$.messageLogs[0].operation", "operator": "eq", "value": "publish" },
        { "path": "$.messageLogs[0].routingKey", "operator": "eq", "value": "order-events" },
        { "path": "$.messageLogs[0].body.orderId", "operator": "eq", "value": 42 }
      ]
    }
  ]
}`} lang="json" />

  <h3>Example: match block for filtering</h3>
  <CodeBlock code={`{
  "name": "Find publish to specific exchange",
  "action": { "type": "wait", "durationMs": 500 },
  "assertions": [
    {
      "match": {
        "path": "$.messageLogs",
        "where": [
          { "path": "$$.operation", "operator": "eq", "value": "publish" },
          { "path": "$$.exchange", "operator": "eq", "value": "events" }
        ],
        "count": 1
      },
      "assertions": [
        { "path": "$.match.body.type", "operator": "eq", "value": "order.created" }
      ]
    }
  ]
}`} lang="json" />
</DocsLayout>
